%2C%20several%20posts%20were%20vacated%20during%20winter%2C%20but%20some%20%26quot%3Bwinter%20cut-off%20posts%26quot%3B%20were%20still%20held%2C%20and%20the%20Army's%20Aviation%20Corps%20conducted%20Winter%20Air%20Surveillance%20Operations%20(WASO)%20for%20reconnaissance.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAmidst%20the%20Lahore%20Peace%20Summit%20in%201999%2C%20Pakistan%20took%20advantage%20of%20this%20posturing%20and%20occupied%20several%20posts.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20first%20intrusions%20were%20reported%20by%20shepherds%20on%20May%203%20in%20the%20Banju%20area%20of%20Batalik%20Sector%2C%20the%20operational%20area%20of%20the%20121%20Infantry%20Brigade.%20Later%2C%203%20Punjab%20was%20sent%20on%20two%20patrols%20a%20day%20later%2C%20and%20on%20May%206%2C%20more%20intrusions%20were%20detected.%20By%20May%2012%2C%20intrusions%20were%20detected%20in%20multiple%20sectors%2C%20signalling%20a%20larger%20operation.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22Image%20posted%20on%20Facebook%20by%20Krishna%20K%20Chari%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Image%20posted%20on%20Facebook%20by%20Krishna%20K%20Chari%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-06%2Fnbv5oc7_tololing-_625x300_24_June_24.jpeg%3Fim%3DFaceCrop%2Calgorithm%3Ddnn%2Cwidth%3D1200%2Cheight%3D738%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECredits%3A%20Image%20posted%20on%20Facebook%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.facebook.com%2FKrishnachari%3Flocale%3Dkk_KZ%5C%22%3EKrishnachari%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20Kaksar%20sector%2C%20which%20lay%20east%20of%20Dras%2C%20a%20patrol%20of%204%20Jat%20under%20Captain%20Saurabh%20Kalia's%20command%20saw%20the%20enemy%20at%20Bajrang%20Post.%20Captain%20Kalia%20and%20his%20men%20were%20captured%20and%20brutally%20tortured%20to%20death%20for%20several%20days.%20In%20Turtuk%2C%20Pakistani%20helicopters%20were%20spotted%20in%20the%20last%20week%20of%20April%20with%20an%20underslung%20load%2C%20and%20later%20in%20May%2C%20a%20patrol%20of%2012%20Jat%20was%20ambushed%20near%20the%20LoC.%20Subsequent%20patrols%20were%20sent%20on%20May%2016%20and%2019.%20The%20enemy%20was%20spread%20over%20an%20area%20of%20150%20kilometres.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EBoots%20On%20The%20Ground%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERemobilization%20of%20troops%20began%2C%20and%20a%20mass%20deployment%20started.%20The%203%20Infantry%20Division%20had%20four%20undermanned%20Brigades%20in%20the%20region%3A%20121%20Infantry%20Brigades%20for%20the%20entire%20Kargil%20sector%20deployed%20along%20with%20Ladakh%20Scouts%3B%2070%20Infantry%20Brigades%20in%20Batalik%2C%20with%20two%20battalions%20in%20the%20Central%20Sector%20of%20Siachen%20Glacier%2C%20assisting%20the%20Brigade%20there%3B%20the%20other%20two%20battalions%20were%20involved%20in%20counter-terrorism%20operations%20in%20Kashmir.%20The%20third%20was%20the%20114%20Infantry%20Brigade%2C%20also%20known%20as%20the%20Siachen%20Brigade.%20The%20fourth%20brigade%20of%203%20Inf%20Div%20was%20the%20102%20Infantry%20Brigade%2C%20responsible%20for%20the%20southern%20sectors%20of%20Siachen.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Army%20faced%20setbacks%20during%20the%20early%20days%20of%20the%20conflict%20when%20ground%20troops%20were%20deployed%20to%20evict%20the%20enemy.%20The%20Dras%20sector%2C%20which%20was%20closest%20to%20the%20Line%20of%20Control%2C%20was%20the%20most%20vulnerable%20to%20the%20enemy's%20precision%20artillery%20fire%20on%20Indian%20convoys.%20The%20uphill%20battle%20at%2018%2C000%20feet%20meant%2010%20Indian%20soldiers%20were%20needed%20to%20evict%20one%20intruder.%20The%20initial%20fog%20of%20war%20led%20to%20several%20casualties%2C%20and%20an%20air%20assault%20was%20necessary.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E'Air%20Force%20Enters'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Chiefs%20of%20Staff%20Committee%20(COSC)%20was%20headed%20by%20General%20VP%20Malik.%20The%20Cabinet%20Security%20on%20Security%20(CCS)%2C%20headed%20by%20Prime%20Minister%20AB%20Vajpayee%2C%20was%20initially%20reluctant%20to%20deploy%20attack%20helicopters%20to%20avoid%20an%20escalation.%20General%20Malik%2C%20in%20his%20book%20'India's%20Military%20Conflicts%20and%20Diplomacy'%2C%20writes%20that%20the%20CCS%20was%20initially%20reluctant%20to%20deploy%20attack%20helicopters%20to%20avoid%20an%20escalation.%20He%20writes%20that%20before%20his%20return%20from%20overseas%2C%20Air%20Chief%20Marshal%20AY%20Tipnis%20was%20not%20ready%20to%20use%20air%20power.%20Firstly%2C%20attack%20helicopters%20like%20Mi-25%2F35%20could%20not%20fly%20at%20that%20altitude%2C%20and%20secondly%2C%20the%20escalation%20of%20conflict.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-06%2Fkn0ns9ig_operation-safed-sagar_625x300_24_June_24.jpeg%3Fim%3DFaceCrop%2Calgorithm%3Ddnn%2Cwidth%3D1200%2Cheight%3D738%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EPhoto%20Credit%3A%20Image%20posted%20on%20X%20by%20%40IAF_MCC%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAir%20Marshal%20Arjun%20Subramaniam%20in%20his%20book%20'Full%20Spectrum'%20writes%20that%20the%20IAF%20chief%20said%20he%20was%20not%20kept%20in%20the%20loop%20during%20the%20initial%20days%20of%20war%20and%20therefore%20there%20was%20pressure%20on%20him%20to%20deliver.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThen%20foreign%20minister%20Jaswant%20Singh%20on%20May%2018%2C%201999%2C%20had%20opposed%20the%20idea%20of%20deploying%20IAF%20and%20the%20Navy%2C%20but%20on%20May%2025%2C%20a%20go-ahead%20was%20given%20to%20deploy%20fighters.%20Though%20the%20IAF%20had%20been%20providing%20air%20support%20to%20the%20army%20since%20May%2017%2C%20for%20the%20first%20time%20a%20go-ahead%20was%20given%20for%20combat%20ops%20but%20with%20a%20caveat%3A%20%26quot%3BDo%20not%20cross%20the%20Line%20of%20Control%26quot%3B.%20The%20IAF%20was%20not%20kept%20in%20the%20loop%20between%20May%207%20and%20May%2015%20by%20the%20army%20in%20operational%20planning%20and%20only%20sought%20chopper%20support.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20area%20of%20intrusion%20in%20a%20sector%20was%20limited%20to%20five%20to%2010%20kilometres%2C%20and%20the%20restriction%20to%20not%20cross%20the%20LOC%20meant%20the%20aircraft%20flying%20close%20to%20enemy%20positions.%20The%20bunkers%20were%20camouflaged%2C%20and%20the%20Air%20Force%20never%20conducted%20precision%20strikes%20at%2018%2C000%20feet.%20The%20challenges%20limited%20the%20effectiveness%20of%20bombing%20to%20some%20extent.%20In%201999%2C%20the%20Indian%20Air%20Force%20conducted%20Exercise%20Trishul%20in%20the%20Himalayas%2C%20many%20weeks%20before%20the%20Kargil%20conflict%2C%20flying%20over%205%2C000%20sorties%20for%20high-altitude%20operations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E'Changing%20the%20strategy'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20IAF%20fleet%20had%20two%20MiG-21%2C%20MiG-27%2FMiG-23%20BN%2C%20Jaguar%2C%20and%20Mi-17%20squadrons%20for%20offensive%20operations.%20There%20were%20two%20MiG-29%2C%20one%20MiG-21%2C%20and%20MiG-23%20MF%20squadrons%20for%20air%20defence%20roles.%20Mirage%202000s%20were%20deployed%20for%20offensive%20and%20surveillance%20missions%20along%20with%20Canberra%20photo%20reconnaissance%20bombers%20and%20the%20mighty%20MiG-25%20for%20a%20similar%20role.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20attack%20on%20the%20Tiger%20Hill%20complex%20began%20on%20May%2026%2C%20with%20Mi-17%2C%20MiG-21s%2C%20MiG-23s%2C%20and%20MiG-27s%20taking%20charge.%20Interestingly%2C%20the%20Mi-25%2F35%20attack%20helicopters%20were%20not%20built%20to%20operate%20at%20such%20an%20altitude.%20Guns%20were%20fitted%20on%20Mi-17%20for%20attack%20roles%2C%20an%20Indian%20'jugaad'%20that%20worked%20effectively.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20May%2021%2C%20a%20Canberra%20bomber%20on%20a%20reconnaissance%20mission%20was%20hit%20by%20a%20US-made%20shoulder-fired%2C%20Stinger%2C%20Surface-to-Air%20Missile%20(SAM).%20The%20aircraft%20managed%20to%20land%20back%20safely%2C%20but%20the%20threat%20of%20SAMs%20became%20imminent.%20On%20May%2027%2C%20a%20MiG-27%20piloted%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fcaptured-tortured-by-pak-and-still-an-iaf-pilot-a-kargil-heros-story-1434437%5C%22%3EFlight%20Lieutenant%20Nachiketa%20Rao%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20lost%20over%20the%20Batalik%20sector%20due%20to%20an%20engine%20flameout.%20Flt%20Lt%20Rao%20managed%20to%20eject%2C%20but%20his%20location%20was%20unknown.%20Squadron%20Leader%20Ajay%20Ahuja%2C%20piloting%20a%20MiG-21%2C%20tried%20to%20ascertain%20the%20MiG-27's%20wreckage's%20location%20and%20was%20hit%20by%20an%20enemy%20SAM.%20He%20ejected%20but%20was%20on%20the%20other%20side%20of%20the%20LOC%20and%20was%20captured%20and%20brutally%20tortured%20by%20the%20Pakistani%20troops.%20The%20next%20day%2C%20a%20Mi-17%20helicopter%20was%20the%20target%20of%20the%20Stinger%20missile%20while%20it%20was%20attacking%20the%20Tololing%20peak.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.ndtvimg.com%2Fi%2F2016-07%2Fgroup-captain-nachiketa-with-parents-650_650x400_71469112031.jpg%3Fim%3DFaceCrop%2Calgorithm%3Ddnn%2Cwidth%3D1200%2Cheight%3D738%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(Flight%20Lieutenant%20(Later%20Group%20Captain)%20Nachiketa%20with%20his%20parents%20a%20day%20after%20returning%20to%20India%20after%20his%20release)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20IAF%20recalibrated%20its%20strategy.%20Attack%20helicopters%20were%20not%20deployed%20for%20such%20roles%2C%20and%20they%20were%20more%20vulnerable%20to%20SAMs%20and%20air%20defence%20guns.%20Installing%20flares%20to%20counter%20missile%20attacks%20and%20flying%20at%2030%2C000%20feet%20as%20the%20Stinger%20could%20not%20operate%20at%20such%20altitude.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKaiser%20Tufail%2C%20a%20former%20Pakistan%20Air%20Force%20pilot%2C%20in%20his%20blog%20'Aeronaut'%2C%20writes%20the%20Pakistani%20version%20of%20operational%20planning%20and%20said%20that%20X%20Corps%20commander%20Lt%20General%20Mahmood%20Ahmed%20broke%20the%20news%20of%20a%20limited%20operation%20across%20the%20LOC.%20During%20the%20operation%20briefing%2C%20Lt%20Gen%20Mahmood%20was%20asked%20the%20type%20of%20air%20support%20the%20troops%20needed%2C%20to%20which%20he%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20have%20Stingers%20on%20every%20peak%26quot%3B.%20Air%20Commodore%20Saleem%20Nawaz%20asked%20him%20if%20these%20missiles%20have%20a%20limited%20attack%20envelope%20and%20it%20doesn't%20stop%20the%20IAF%20and%20artillery%20from%20attacking%20us%20from%20high%20altitude%2C%20to%20which%20Lt%20Gen%20Mahmood%20said%2C%20our%20troops%20were%20well%20positioned%20and%20concealed%20and%20the%20IAF%20wouldn't%20be%20able%20to%20pick%20it%20up%20from%20the%20air.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EIAF%20in%20full%20force%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%20initial%20days%20of%20its%20offensive%20operations%2C%20the%20aircraft%20used%20rockets%20and%20guns%20to%20attack%20the%20crest%20of%20the%20mountain%20peak%2C%20for%20which%20they%20had%20to%20dive%20low%2C%20attack%2C%20and%20then%20pull%20quickly.%20This%20manoeuvre%20made%20them%20vulnerable%20to%20SAMs.%20After%20Sq%20Ldr%20Ajay%20Ahuja's%20capture%2C%20all%20low-level%20flights%20were%20abandoned%2C%20and%20only%20medium-level%20strikes%20were%20sanctioned.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-06%2Fdil74hs8_iaf-kargil-bomb-photo_625x300_24_June_24.jpeg%3Fim%3DFitAndFill%2Calgorithm%3Ddnn%2Cwidth%3D1200%2Cheight%3D738%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E250%20kg%20and%20500%20kg%20dumb%20bombs%20were%20dropped%2C%20and%20relentless%20bombing%20of%20peaks%20in%20the%20Tiger%20Hill%20complex%20began.%20Fighter%20jets%20would%20first%20conduct%20strikes%2C%20and%20later%20army%20operations%20were%20conducted.%20The%20strikes%20by%20Mirage%202000%20on%20Muntho%20Dhalo%20in%20the%20Batalik%20sector%2C%20a%20logistics%20headquarters%2C%20turned%20the%20tide.%20On%20June%2016%2C%20Mirage%202000s%20attacked%20the%20logistics%20camp%20with%2036%20250-kg%20bombs%2C%20which%20destroyed%20the%20supply%20lines%20to%20forward%20troops%20in%20Batalik%20and%20Kaksar.%20It%20was%20followed%20by%20attacks%20on%20Kukarthang%2C%20a%20fuel%20dump%20supply%2C%20struck%20by%20MiG-27.%20The%20post%20was%20re-taken%20by%201%2F11%20Gorkha%20Rifles%20later.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETwenty-five%20years%20ago%2C%20on%20June%2024%2C%201999%2C%20Wing%20Commander%20Raghunath%20Nambiar%20and%20Sqn%20Leader%20Monish%20Yadav%20from%207%20Squadron%20flew%20the%20first%20mission%20over%20Tiger%20Hill%20where%20precision%20strikes%20using%20the%20Israeli%20'Litening%20Pod'%20was%20used.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fblog%2Fhow-i-bombed-tiger-hill-from-a-mirage-2000-2075280%5C%22%3EAir%20Marshal%20Nambiar%20in%20an%20NDTV%20column%20said%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%26quot%3BThe%20Laser%20was%20steadily%20flashing%2C%20and%20we%20waited%20anxiously%20for%20the%20target%20to%20explode%2C%20thus%20signalling%20a%20successful%20delivery.%20The%20time%20of%20flight%20of%20an%20LGB%20under%20the%20delivery%20conditions%20that%20we%20had%20dropped%20it%20in%20was%20under%2030%20seconds%2C%20but%20to%20us%20in%20the%20cockpit%2C%20it%20appeared%20as%20an%20eternity.%20Our%20joy%20knew%20no%20bounds%20as%20the%20entire%20video%20image%20of%20the%20target%20burst%20out%20into%20a%20soundless%20explosion.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%20class%3D%5C%22twitter-tweet%5C%22%20data-conversation%3D%5C%22none%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%20lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fhashtag%2FCrossHair%3Fsrc%3Dhash%26ref_